        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  To define BadFileFormatError — raised when an input file cannot be handled by any reader in the dedoc processing pipeline. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  File format rejection error signalling. \par \b Input\/ \:  Error context (msg, filename, version). \par \b Output\/ \:  BadFileFormatError with HTTP 415 Unsupported Media Type code. \par \b Links\/ \:  [USES_API(9): <ref refid="classdedoc_1_1common_1_1exceptions_1_1dedoc__error_1_1DedocError" kindref="compound">dedoc.common.exceptions.dedoc_error.DedocError</ref>] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>ALWAYS carries HTTP code 415 (Unsupported Media Type).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Inherits full DedocError API (msg_api, filename, version, metadata). \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why hardcode code=415? A: Bad file format is semantically &quot;Unsupported Media Type&quot; in HTTP terms — the client sent a file the server cannot process. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 — Semantic template markup and LDD logging added.] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
<para>CLASS 8[Exception for unreadable file formats, always HTTP 415] =&gt; BadFileFormatError \par \b Use Cases\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>[BadFileFormatError]: Reader → NoReaderFound → RaiseBadFileFormatError → APIResponds415 </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
